<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// numbering of each the machine instructions an interval &#91;i, j) is said to be a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// live range for register v if there is no instruction with number j&#39; &gt;= j</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// such that v is live at j&#39; and there is no instruction with number i&#39; &lt; i such</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that v is live at i&#39;. In this implementation ranges can have holes,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// i.e. a range might look like &#91;1,20), &#91;50,65), &#91;1000,1001).  Each</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// individual segment is represented as an instance of LiveRange::Segment,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and the whole range is represented as an instance of LiveRange.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="17"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1121"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                           LiveRangeUpdater class</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1122"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1123"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1124"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The LiveRangeUpdater class always maintains these invariants:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1125"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1126"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - When LastStart is invalid, Spills is empty and the iterators are invalid.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1127"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   This is the initial state, and the state created by flush().</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1128"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   In this state, isDirty() returns false.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1129"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1130"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Otherwise, segments are kept in three separate areas:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1131"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1132"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 &#91;begin; WriteI) at the front of LR.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1133"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 2 &#91;ReadI; end) at the back of LR.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1134"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 3 Spills.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1135"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1136"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - LR.begin() &lt;= WriteI &lt;= ReadI &lt;= LR.end().</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1137"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Segments in all three areas are fully ordered and coalesced.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1138"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Segments in area 1 precede and can&#39;t coalesce with segments in area 2</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1139"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Segments in Spills precede and can&#39;t coalesce with segments in area 2</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1140"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - No coalescing is possible between segments in Spills and segments in area</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1141"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   1, and there are no overlapping segments.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1142"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1143"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The segments in Spills are not ordered with respect to the segments in area</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01144" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1144"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 They need to be merged.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01145" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1145"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1146"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// When they exist, Spills.back().start &lt;= LastStart,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1147"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                 and WriteI&#91;-1&#93;.start &lt;= LastStart.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01148" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1148"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01149" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1149"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM&#95;ENABLE&#95;DUMP)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01274" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1274"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> LiveRangeUpdater::mergeSpills() &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01275" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1275"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Perform a backwards merge of Spills and &#91;SpillI;WriteI).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01276" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1276"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">size&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> GapSize = ReadI - WriteI;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01277" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1277"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">size&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> NumMoved = std::min(Spills.size(), GapSize);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01278" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1278"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liverange/#a143c1fcb6066cb301f828ec4c18d79f4">LiveRange::iterator</a> Src = WriteI;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01282" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1282"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01284" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1284"><span class="doxyHighlight">  WriteI = Dst;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01285" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1285"></CodeLine>
